## 2026-07-04 — Generalize catalog to unified `media` + normalized taxonomies + full CRUD
- What:
  - Migration 0004: renamed table `manga`→`media` (+ `type` manga|video|novel),
    renamed FK columns to `media_id`, normalized genre/category/author/artist into
    tables + join tables, back-filled existing genres(CSV)/author/artist.
  - Domain: `Manga`→`Media` (+ `Type`, name-array taxonomies), `Chapter.MediaID`,
    generic `Taxonomy`/`TaxonomyKind`, `MediaWriteRequest`/`ChapterWriteRequest`/
    `TaxonomyWriteRequest`, `CatalogFilter` type + category dimensions.
  - Repo: `MangaRepo`→`MediaRepo`; group_concat(char(31)) taxonomy subqueries;
    filter rewrite (type IN + genre/category EXISTS/COUNT); media/chapter CRUD +
    taxonomy CRUD (`taxTableFor` allowlist). `job_repo` media_id.
  - Services: `MangaService`→`MediaService` + media/chapter CRUD; new
    `TaxonomyService`. Handlers: `MediaHandler` + `TaxonomyHandler`; routes replace
    `/v1/manga*` with `/v1/media*`, add `/v1/taxonomies/{kind}`, gate management
    behind manga.write.
  - Full API replace (breaking): see docs/api-migration-media.md for the iOS agent.
- Why: client consumes one endpoint set for all media kinds (type discriminator);
  proper management + normalized, deduplicated taxonomies.
- Files: migrations/0004_media_normalize.sql; internal/domain/{manga,convert}.go;
  internal/repository/d1/{media_repo,job_repo,ports}.go; internal/service/{ports,
  media_service,taxonomy_service,convert_service}.go; internal/handler/{ports,
  media_handler,taxonomy_handler,response}.go; internal/server/router.go;
  internal/app/module.go; .mockery.yaml + regenerated mocks + swagger; CLAUDE.md;
  docs/api-migration-media.md.
- Tests: rewrote repo/service/handler tests, added client + novel + taxonomy +
  CRUD + error-path coverage. `go build/vet` clean; `go test ./...` → 159 pass;
  gated pkg coverage: domain 100%, service 89.8%, handler 88.2%, d1 82.2% (all ≥80%).

