## 2026-07-05 — /v1/users responses use the uniform envelope
- What: user_admin.go respondData/respondErr now emit domain.APIResponse (was
  bare c.JSON + {error,message}), so admin user-management matches every other
  REST endpoint post response-envelope migration.
- Why: the response-envelope change wrapped all handlers, but the concurrently
  developed /v1/users endpoints were written against the old bare shape, leaving
  them the only inconsistent surface. The admin FE's request() client is being
  updated to unwrap the envelope centrally, which requires /v1/users to conform.
- Files: internal/oidc/user_admin.go
- Tests: go build ./... + go vet ./internal/oidc/... clean; go test ./... → 210 pass.
